data.description: We would prefer  24 hour Notice for all  showings, the seller and listing agent will be AT ALL SHOWINGS.  This Victorian Home was built by Joney Levy in 1903 for the Family Home.  When entering through the iron gate, you will love the screen in porch, with adjustable  shades by C BEL awnings on New Orleans.   The resident  features 3 bedrooms, (could be 4) and 1 full bathroom with 1/2 bath in with the LARGE laundry room.  There is a SUNKEN TUB in an enclosure area that the owner  created for it,  on the back porch  of the home, with an on-demand water heater.  In 2015-16 new windows, painting, new steps, 1 new a/c, new cabinets, doors and NO carpet, beaded board,  teak cypress and wallpaper  you will find in the home.  The kitchen features Walnut  flooring, farmhouse sink, Beaded Board ceiling, with cabinet reaching to the ceiling..12 foot ceiling throughout the home. This property is on .87 on acre and it Does have a detach garage and storage, great area!!   Home has a large foyer, such  charm in  this home.  Call for your private showing.....
